social_posts.post_text: started 2022 off losing my best friend and ended it with gaining another. this year has been life changing to say the least but beyond blessed to enter 2023 with these peeps by my side. stay safe tonight y’all 🫡

hey IG 👋 haven’t posted this year as i’ve been raising a mini scotterly and being a daddy (not the fatherhood type). I still plan on doing videos and getting back at the content game but in the meantime enjoy a collage of this year so far

365 days without you. i owe y’all an explanation of why I been MIA as I’ve always said I’d be open with you guys about who I am on this account. this past year has been the most difficult part of my life. From losing my best friend to drama in my personal life, I didn’t think I’d hit such a low. I’ve battled adversity before in my life and have reminded myself to be grateful and blessed of the good things I have. But after losing Kai, I went into a dark hole. Depression, lack of motivation, drinking heavily, etc tore me up. I had good days ofc but would then remind myself he’s no longer here and instantly blame myself and go back to day one. It wasn’t until Theo was born where i decided to piece myself back together. To tell you the truth, if it wasn’t for him (and my super amazing loving fiancé) idk where I’d be. Don’t think I’ve ever been this open with y’all but you guys deserve to know why I’ve barely posted over the past year. I won’t ever forget Kai and the memories I have of him but it’s time to continue with my life and make more new memories with those i love around me. You don’t ever move on from a loss like that, you simply learn to live with it. If you’re going through a dark time, just know it gets better.. you just need to take it one day at a time, one step at a time. Love y’all

yours truly, 
scotterly
someone told my son that his dad has the most basic tattoo known to man and that he’s also one of the finest individuals out there.. one is a fact and one is a lie. you choose.

a week ago today my mom suffered a heart attack and flatlined. Her heart rate jumped to 250 bpm and then she was gone. Three shocks to her chest and 60 seconds later, she came back. Immediately was rushed into emergency heart surgery and placed into intubation. After countless procedures, my mom is walking again and set to go home this week. If it wasn’t for the amazing team at Baylor Scott & White and the doctors who performed under pressure, she wouldn’t be alive today. My mom still has quite the journey to full recovery but she’s still here and that’s all that matters. Don’t ever take for granted the time you have left with your parents or loved ones.. call em, visit, check in. Me included. Love y’all 🫶🏼
